[p 
	"After the end of each battle group, I destroyed both ships together, to
	$LF
	"save the time of the last victory ditty. With the exception of the battle
	$LF
	"fought by Fwiffo (Spathi); I needed to sell Fwiffo's ship, and therefore
	$LF
	"I couldn't have it destroyed in the battle.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"I admit the battles could be improved a lot with techniques like
	$LF
	"luck manipulation (for the starting position&orientation of the
	$LF
	"enemy ship relative to own ship) and using improved fighting strategies.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Details:
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Ilwrath
	]b
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Three BUTT missiles and one pellet. The most accurate
	$LF
	"and fastest way to kill the Ilwrath with a Spathi ship.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Mycon
	]b
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Because the Pkunk Fury has low firepower and the Mycon Podship has high firepower,
	$LF
	"my strategy involved having the Mycon finish itself off. So I purposefully
	$LF
	"avoided shooting the Mycon from behind 
	[em 
		"until
	]em
	" it has shot at least two
	$LF
	"plasma blasts. (Doing otherwise means the Mycon will spend its resources
	$LF
	"to regenerate crew instead.) After the blasts appear, I maneuver the
	$LF
	"Fury to a position such that the Mycon ship will end up being in
	$LF
	"the between of the plasma blasts and the Fury, forcing the Mycon
	$LF
	"to receive its own blasts. They do a lot of damage.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"For one of the five battles, I demonstrated the inferior strategy.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The last battle was most difficult because I had to make sure that the Mycon
	$LF
	"and the Pkunk die almost at the same time. But it ended up being the fastest.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Umgah
	]b
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Both the Arilou Skiff and the Umgah Drone have low firepower.
	$LF
	"Both have very erratic
	$LF
	"maneuverability. My strategy involved staying immobile beside the enemy
	$LF
	"ship and just shooting it. However, the Umgah is keen to use its special
	$LF
	"function; superspeed backwards teleport. So I had to occassionally keep
	$LF
	"up with the movement.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Druuge
	]b
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The Druuge Mauler and the Earthling Cruiser are quite similar design.
	$LF
	"Both are narrow and long, and both fire projectiles that travel far.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"But the differences end there: The Mauler regenerates batteries by
	$LF
	"tossing their crew into the furnaces, and they fire tiny, extremely
	$LF
	"powerful and high-velocity projectiles that travel straight, causing
	$LF
	"a huge of recoil to the firing ship, whereas the Cruiser fires homing
	$LF
	"missiles and has the ability to laser-zap close-by offenders. There is
	$LF
	"nothing special to the strategy employed here; I simply try to ensure
	$LF
	"that all the missiles hit their target.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Like in the Arilou-Umgah battle, I gradually sacrificed the crew in the
	$LF
	"Cruiser to enable it to be killed at the same time as the last Mauler.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Ur-Quan and Kohr-Ah
	]b
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"My first plan was to annihilate all six ships with a single Utwig Jugger.
	$LF
	"After the third try, I came up with another plan; using three pairs of ships:
	$LF
	"Two Chmmr Avatars, two Orz Nemesises and two Utwig Juggers. By dedicating
	$LF
	"each battle its own ship, I can have them always destroyed at the end of
	$LF
	"the battle together with the enemy. I chose three different ship types
	$LF
	"instead of one or two for better entertainment. 
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"In the Chmmr vs Kohr-Ah battle, it turns out I misestimated the amount of crew
	$LF
	"needed aboard the Avatar. The battle didn't go as I wanted. Hence, I ended
	$LF
	"up having one excess ship at the end. If I had correctly estimated the amount
	$LF
	"of crew needed, the Avatar would have been destroyed together with the Marauder.
	$LF
	"I tried to hex-edit it, but it resulted in desyncs, and because every battle is
	$LF
	"different, the amount would have been wrong again.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Sa-matra
	]b
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The Avatar's zapstats were very useful against the Sa-Matra's
	$LF
	"shields, conserving the power of the main weapon.
	$LF
]p
[h4 
	" Luck manipulation
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"In Star Control II, the randomness is updated every time it is requested.
	$LF
	"Unlike in NES games, this randomness does not sample any information about
	$LF
	"the game state.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"You can only influence the randomness by influencing the 
	[em 
		"need
	]em
	" for
	$LF
	"randomness. For example, when you enter a solar system, the configuration
	$LF
	"of enemy ships in the solar system is decided. To influence that, you need
	$LF
	"to enter the solar system later or sooner and from different positions on
	$LF
	"the map. This helps, because the hyperspace view uses the randomness function
	$LF
	"to decide the appearance of other hyperspace travellers
	$LF
	"(especially the Slylandro Probes), as a function of proximity
	$LF
	"to different spheres of influence.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"To influence the randomness used to displace the planet lander from its
	$LF
	"intended destination, you need to first influence the randomness calls
	$LF
	"done in the solar system to permutate the actions of the enemy ships
	$LF
	"flying there.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"In Mycon-Pkunk battles, the Pkunk's insult words are selected randomly.
	$LF
	"Hence, your decision of whether or not to insult, will influence the enemy
	$LF
	"ship's spawn location. (The Pkunk ship insults the opponent in order to
	$LF
	"recharge its own batteries. This is the action of the spacebar button.)
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Details about the route
	$LF
]h3
[h4 
	" Beginning
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"I harvested Io for precious radioactives. I also harvested Mercury. And Luna.
	$LF
	"This time-wasting diversion not only gained me enough resources to maximize
	$LF
